A Polygamous husband (63) is on the run after he allegedly shot and killed his second wife (53) to death. According to the police, the couple from Malamulele outside Giyani in Limpopo allegedly had a quarrel which ended deadly on Saturday night, 6 February. Police spokesman Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the suspect then produced his licensed firearm and shot his wife several times. “The police were called and on arrival, the suspect had already fled the scene. The firearm that was allegedly used in the murder was found and confiscated. “Our preliminary investigations revealed that the motive for the incident may be related to domestic violence,” Ngoepe said. Provincial commissioner Lieutenant-General Nneke Ledwaba condemned the incident and has since directed the suspect be hunted down until he is brought to book. Anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspect should call Lieutenant-Colonel Thifhelimbilu Makunge on 082 729 0229, the CrimeStop on 08600 10111, the nearest police station or send information to MySAPSApp.